label: Switch
comment: A SwitchSchedule is associated with a Switch.

label: Curve
comment: The curve of  this curve data point.

label: endDate
comment: Date season ends.

label: maxP
comment: Maximum active power of the injection.

label: maxQ
comment: Maximum reactive power limit. It is used for modelling of infeed for load flow exchange and not for short circuit modelling.

label: maxIdc
comment: The maximum direct current (Id) on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data use in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: minP
comment: Minimum active power of the injection.

label: qFrequencyExponent
comment: Exponent of per unit frequency effecting reactive power.

label: capacitance
comment: Capacitance of the DC shunt.

label: totalEfficiency
comment: The efficiency of the unit in converting the fuel into electrical energy.

label: resistance
comment: Resistance of the DC line segment.

label: maxModulationIndex
comment: The maximum quotient between the AC converter voltage (Uc) and DC voltage (Ud). A factor typically less than 1. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow.

label: ratedPowerFactor
comment: Power factor (nameplate data). It is primarily used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909. The attribute cannot be a negative value.

label: idleLoss
comment: Active power loss in pole at no power transfer. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: GeneratingUnit
comment: A synchronous machine may operate as a generator and as such becomes a member of a generating unit.

label: RotatingMachine
comment: The synchronous machine drives the turbine which moves the water from a low elevation to a higher elevation. The direction of machine rotation for pumping may or may not be the same as for generating.

label: endNumber
comment: Number for this transformer end, corresponding to the end's order in the power transformer vector group or phase angle clock number.  Highest voltage winding should be 1.  Each end within a power transformer should have a unique subsequent end number.   Note the transformer end number need not match the terminal sequence number.

label: shortPF
comment: Generating unit short term economic participation factor.

label: pConstantImpedance
comment: Portion of active power load modelled as constant impedance.

label: step
comment: The tap step.

label: xMax
comment: The reactance depends on the tap position according to a "u" shaped curve. The maximum reactance (xMax) appears at the low and high tap positions. Depending on the “u” curve the attribute can be either higher or lower than PowerTransformerEnd.x.

label: lowStep
comment: Lowest possible tap step position, retard from neutral.

label: maxQ
comment: Maximum reactive power limit. This is the maximum (nameplate) limit for the unit.

label: qfixedPct
comment: Fixed reactive power as a percentage of load group fixed reactive power. Used to represent the time-varying components.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

label: minAlpha
comment: Minimum firing angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: maxP
comment: Maximum active power limit. This is the maximum (nameplate) limit for the unit.

label: ratedU
comment:
Rated voltage (nameplate data, Ur in IEC 60909-0). It is primarily used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: windGenUnitType
comment: The kind of wind generating unit.

label: nominalFrequency
comment: Nameplate data indicates if the machine is 50 Hz or 60 Hz.

label: gch
comment: Positive sequence shunt (charging) conductance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.

label: nominalVoltage
comment: Phase-to-phase nominal voltage.

label: VoltageLevel
comment: The voltage level containing this bay.

label: Substation
comment: The substation of the voltage level.

label: inductance
comment: Inductance of the device.

label: nominalVoltage
comment: The power system resource's base voltage.  Shall be a positive value and not zero.

label: PowerTransformer
comment: The power transformer of this power transformer end.

label: qConstantImpedance
comment: Portion of reactive power load modelled as constant impedance.

label: retained
comment: Branch is retained in the topological solution.  The flow through retained switches will normally be calculated in power flow.

label: Terminal
comment: Terminal of the power transformer to which this transformer end belongs.

label: nomU
comment: The voltage at which the nominal reactive power may be calculated. This should normally be within 10% of the voltage at which the capacitor is connected to the network.

label: ThermalGeneratingUnit
comment: A thermal generating unit may have one or more fossil fuels.

label: voltageSensitivity
comment: Voltage sensitivity required for the device to regulate the bus voltage, in voltage/reactive power.

label: normalSections
comment: The normal number of sections switched in. The value shall be between zero and ShuntCompensator.maximumSections.

label: switchingLoss
comment: Switching losses, relative to the base apparent power 'baseS'. Refer to poleLossP. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: Terminal
comment: The terminal to which this tie flow belongs.

label: fossilFuelType
comment: The type of fossil fuel, such as coal, oil, or gas.

label: ratedNetMaxP
comment:
The net rated maximum capacity determined by subtracting the auxiliary power used to operate the internal plant machinery from the rated gross maximum capacity.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: xUnit
comment: The X-axis units of measure.

label: normalValue
comment: The normal value for limit on current flow. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: positiveFlowIn
comment: Specifies the sign of the tie flow associated with a control area. True if positive flow into the terminal (load convention) is also positive flow into the control area.  See the description of ControlArea for further explanation of how TieFlow.positiveFlowIn is used.

label: ConductingEquipment
comment: The conducting equipment of the terminal.  Conducting equipment have  terminals that may be connected to other conducting equipment terminals via connectivity nodes or topological nodes.

label: isInfiniteDuration
comment: Defines if the operational limit type has infinite duration. If true, the limit has infinite duration. If false, the limit has definite duration which is defined by the attribute acceptableDuration.

label: b
comment: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance per section.

label: startDate
comment: Date season starts.

label: LoadArea
comment: The LoadArea where the SubLoadArea belongs.

label: turbineType
comment: Type of turbine.

label: sectionNumber
comment: The number of the section.

label: EnergySchedulingType
comment: Energy Scheduling Type of an Energy Source.

label: DCConductingEquipment
comment: An DC  terminal belong to a DC conducting equipment.

label: ControlArea
comment: The control area of the tie flows.

label: hydroPlantStorageType
comment: The type of hydro power plant water storage.

label: lengthFromTerminal1
comment: The length to the place where the clamp is located starting from side one of the line segment, i.e. the line segment terminal with sequence number equal to 1.

label: NonConformLoadGroup
comment: The NonConformLoadGroup where the NonConformLoadSchedule belongs.

label: direction
comment: The direction of the limit.

label: RegulatingControl
comment: Regulating controls that have this schedule.

label: minGamma
comment: Minimum extinction angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: HydroPowerPlant
comment: The hydro pump may be a member of a pumped storage plant or a pump for distributing water.

label: toEndName
comment:
A human readable name with length of the string 64 characters maximum. It covers the following two cases:
-if the Boundary point is placed on a tie-line, it is the name (IdentifiedObject.name) of the substation at which the "To" side of the tie-line is connected to.
-if the Boundary point is placed in a substation, it is the name (IdentifiedObject.name) of the element (e.g. PowerTransformer, ACLineSegment, Switch, etc.) at which the "To" side of the Boundary point is connected to.

label: maxAlpha
comment: Maximum firing angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: b
comment: Magnetizing branch susceptance (B mag).  The value can be positive or negative.

label: qConstantPower
comment: Portion of reactive power load modelled as constant power.

label: inductiveRating
comment: Inductive reactance at maximum inductive reactive power.  Shall always be negative.

label: y2Unit
comment: The Y2-axis units of measure.

label: BaseVoltage
comment: Base voltage of this conducting equipment.  Use only when there is no voltage level container used and only one base voltage applies.  For example, not used for transformers.

label: maxUdc
comment: The maximum voltage on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: pfixedPct
comment: Fixed active power as a percentage of load group fixed active power. Used to represent the time-varying components.  Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

label: voltageStepIncrement
comment:
The voltage step increment on the out of phase winding (the PowerTransformerEnd where the TapChanger is located) specified in percent of rated voltage of the PowerTransformerEnd. A positive value means a positive voltage variation from the Terminal at the PowerTransformerEnd, where the TapChanger is located, into the transformer.
When the increment is negative, the voltage decreases when the tap step increases.

label: ConnectivityNode
comment: The connectivity node that is designated as a boundary point.

label: maximumAllowableSpinningReserve
comment: Maximum allowable spinning reserve. Spinning reserve will never be considered greater than this value regardless of the current operating point.

label: qConstantCurrent
comment: Portion of reactive power load modelled as constant current.

label: length
comment: Segment length for calculating line section capabilities.

label: LoadGroup
comment: Group of this ConformLoad.

label: PhaseTapChangerTable
comment: The table of this point.

label: ConnectivityNode
comment: The connectivity node to which this terminal connects with zero impedance.

label: Region
comment: The SubGeographicalRegion containing the DC line.

label: normalValue
comment: The normal value of active power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: ratedS
comment:
Nameplate apparent power rating for the unit.
The attribute shall have a positive value.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: nominalP
comment:
The nominal power of the generating unit.  Used to give precise meaning to percentage based attributes such as the governor speed change droop (governorSCD attribute).
The attribute shall be a positive value equal to or less than RotatingMachine.ratedS.

label: NonlinearShuntCompensator
comment: Non-linear shunt compensator owning this point.

label: qPercent
comment: Part of the coordinated reactive control that comes from this machine. The attribute is used as a participation factor not necessarily summing up to 100% for the participating devices in the control.

label: maxP
comment: Maximum active power of the injection.

label: Region
comment: The SubGeographicalRegion containing the substation.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: x
comment:
The series reactance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual reactance is calculated as follows:
calculated reactance = x(nominal) * (1 + x(from this class)/100).   The x(nominal) is defined as the static series reactance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

label: ACLineSegment
comment: The line segment to which the cut is applied.

label: minIdc
comment: The minimum direct current (Id) on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: startupCost
comment: The initial startup cost incurred for each start of the GeneratingUnit.

label: genControlSource
comment: The source of controls for a generating unit.  Defines the control status of the generating unit.

label: governorSCD
comment: Governor Speed Changer Droop.   This is the change in generator power output divided by the change in frequency normalized by the nominal power of the generator and the nominal frequency and expressed in percent and negated. A positive value of speed change droop provides additional generator output upon a drop in frequency.

label: minP
comment: Minimum active power limit. The value is overwritten by values of VsCapabilityCurve, if present.

label: type
comment: The primary type of control area definition used to determine if this is used for automatic generation control, for planning interchange control, or other purposes.   A control area specified with primary type of automatic generation control could still be forecast and used as an interchange area in power flow analysis.

label: minP
comment: Minimum active power limit. This is the minimum (nameplate) limit for the unit.

label: BaseVoltage
comment: Base voltage of the transformer end.  This is essential for PU calculation.

label: numberOfValves
comment: Number of valves in the converter. Used in loss calculations.

label: minP
comment: Minimum active power of the injection.

label: r
comment:
Resistance (star-model) of the transformer end.
The attribute shall be equal to or greater than zero for non-equivalent transformers.

label: SubLoadArea
comment: The SubLoadArea where the Loadgroup belongs.

label: ratedGrossMinP
comment:
The gross rated minimum generation level which the unit can safely operate at while delivering power to the transmission grid.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: highVoltageLimit
comment:
The bus bar's high voltage limit.
The limit applies to all equipment and nodes contained in a given VoltageLevel. It is not required that it is exchanged in pair with lowVoltageLimit. It is preferable to use operational VoltageLimit, which prevails, if present.

label: y1value
comment: The data value of the  first Y-axis variable, depending on the Y-axis units.

label: PowerElectronicsUnit
comment: An AC network connection may have several power electronics units connecting through it.

label: bPerSection
comment: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance per section.

label: voltageSetPoint
comment: The reactive power output of the SVC is proportional to the difference between the voltage at the regulated bus and the voltage setpoint.  When the regulated bus voltage is equal to the voltage setpoint, the reactive power output is zero.

label: stepPhaseShiftIncrement
comment:
Phase shift per step position. A positive value indicates a positive angle variation from the Terminal at the  PowerTransformerEnd,  where the TapChanger is located, into the transformer.
The actual phase shift increment might be more accurately computed from the symmetrical or asymmetrical models or a tap step table lookup if those are available.

label: Region
comment: The geographical region which this sub-geographical region is within.

label: capacitance
comment: Capacitance of the DC line segment. Significant for cables only.

label: xvalue
comment: The data value of the X-axis variable,  depending on the X-axis units.

label: exponentModel
comment:
Indicates the exponential voltage dependency model is to be used. If false, the coefficient model is to be used.
The exponential voltage dependency model consist of the attributes:
- pVoltageExponent
- qVoltageExponent
- pFrequencyExponent
- qFrequencyExponent.
The coefficient model consist of the attributes:
- pConstantImpedance
- pConstantCurrent
- pConstantPower
- qConstantImpedance
- qConstantCurrent
- qConstantPower.
The sum of pConstantImpedance, pConstantCurrent and pConstantPower shall equal 1.
The sum of qConstantImpedance, qConstantCurrent and qConstantPower shall equal 1.

label: Equipment
comment: The equipment to which the limit set applies.

label: variableCost
comment: The variable cost component of production per unit of ActivePower.

label: aggregate
comment:
The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail.  In case the flag is set to “true” the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.  
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

label: sVCControlMode
comment: SVC control mode.

label: normalStep
comment:
The tap step position used in "normal" network operation for this winding. For a "Fixed" tap changer indicates the current physical tap setting.
The attribute shall be equal to or greater than lowStep and equal to or less than highStep.

label: isExcludedFromAreaInterchange
comment: If true, this boundary point is on the interconnection that is excluded from control area interchange calculation and consequently has no related tie flows. Otherwise, the interconnection is included in control area interchange and a TieFlow is required at all sides of the boundary point (default).

label: angle
comment: The angle difference in degrees. A positive value indicates a positive angle variation from the Terminal at the  PowerTransformerEnd,  where the TapChanger is located, into the transformer.

label: DCNode
comment: The DC connectivity node to which this DC base terminal connects with zero impedance.

label: pFrequencyExponent
comment: Exponent of per unit frequency effecting active power.

label: DCEquipmentContainer
comment: The DC container for the DC nodes.

label: sequenceNumber
comment: The orientation of the terminal connections for a multiple terminal conducting equipment.  The sequence numbering starts with 1 and additional terminals should follow in increasing order.   The first terminal is the "starting point" for a two terminal branch.

label: pfixed
comment: Active power of the load that is a fixed quantity and does not vary as load group value varies. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

label: g
comment: Magnetizing branch conductance.

label: priority
comment: Priority of bus name marker for use as topology bus name.  Use 0 for do not care.  Use 1 for highest priority.  Use 2 as priority is less than 1 and so on.

label: EquivalentNetwork
comment: The equivalent where the reduced model belongs.

label: LoadResponse
comment: The load response characteristic of this load.  If missing, this load is assumed to be constant power.

label: resistance
comment: Resistance of the DC device.

label: ratedS
comment:
Normal apparent power rating.
The attribute shall be a positive value. For a two-winding transformer the values for the high and low voltage sides shall be identical.

label: x
comment: Positive sequence reactance.

label: grounded
comment: Used for Yn and Zn connections. True if the neutral is solidly grounded.

label: isDirectCurrent
comment: If true, this boundary point is a point of common coupling (PCC) of a direct current (DC) interconnection, otherwise the interconnection is AC (default).

label: TransformerEnd
comment: Transformer end to which this ratio tap changer belongs.

label: ACLineSegment
comment: The line segment to which the clamp is connected.

label: fromEndIsoCode
comment:
The ISO code of the region which the "From" side of the Boundary point belongs to or it is connected to.
The ISO code is a two-character country code as defined by ISO 3166 (http://www.iso.org/iso/country_codes). The length of the string is 2 characters maximum.

label: pMax
comment: This is the maximum active power that can be produced by the source. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

label: startupTime
comment: Time it takes to get the unit on-line, from the time that the prime mover mechanical power is applied.

label: Substation
comment: The containing substation of the DC converter unit.

label: pMin
comment: This is the minimum active power that can be produced by the source. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a TopologicalNode (bus) into the conducting equipment.

label: InitialReactiveCapabilityCurve
comment: The default reactive capability curve for use by a synchronous machine.

label: ratedU
comment:
Rated voltage: phase-phase for three-phase windings, and either phase-phase or phase-neutral for single-phase windings.
A high voltage side, as given by TransformerEnd.endNumber, shall have a ratedU that is greater than or equal to ratedU for the lower voltage sides.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: normalOpen
comment: The attribute is used in cases when no Measurement for the status value is present. If the Switch has a status measurement the Discrete.normalValue is expected to match with the Switch.normalOpen.

label: maxQ
comment: Maximum reactive power of the injection.  Used for modelling of infeed for load flow exchange. Not used for short circuit modelling.  If maxQ and minQ are not used ReactiveCapabilityCurve can be used.

label: PhaseTapChangerTable
comment: The phase tap changer table for this phase tap changer.

label: neutralStep
comment:
The neutral tap step position for this winding.
The attribute shall be equal to or greater than lowStep and equal or less than highStep.
It is the step position where the voltage is neutralU when the other terminals of the transformer are at the ratedU.  If there are other tap changers on the transformer those taps are kept constant at their neutralStep.

label: g
comment: Positive sequence shunt (charging) conductance per section.

label: dropHeight
comment: The height water drops from the reservoir mid-point to the turbine.

label: fromEndName
comment:
A human readable name with length of the string 64 characters maximum. It covers the following two cases:
-if the Boundary point is placed on a tie-line, it is the name (IdentifiedObject.name) of the substation at which the "From" side of the tie-line is connected to.
-if the Boundary point is placed in a substation, it is the name (IdentifiedObject.name) of the element (e.g. PowerTransformer, ACLineSegment, Switch, etc.) at which the "From" side of the Boundary point is connected to.

label: curveStyle
comment: The style or shape of the curve.

label: OperationalLimitSet
comment: The limit set to which the limit values belong.

label: ratedS
comment:
Nameplate apparent power rating for the unit.
The attribute shall have a positive value.

label: timeStep
comment: The time between each pair of subsequent regular time points in sequence order.

label: y1Unit
comment: The Y1-axis units of measure.

label: polarity
comment:
Represents the normal network polarity condition. Depending on the converter configuration the value shall be set as follows:
- For a monopole with two converter terminals use DCPolarityKind “positive” and “negative”.
- For a bi-pole or symmetric monopole with three converter terminals use DCPolarityKind “positive”, “middle” and “negative”.

label: value2
comment: The second value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the derived type of the associated schedule.

label: ControlArea
comment: The parent control area for the generating unit specifications.

label: qVoltageExponent
comment: Exponent of per unit voltage effecting reactive power.

label: WindPowerPlant
comment: A wind power plant may have wind generating units.

label: maxGamma
comment: Maximum extinction angle. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: highStep
comment:
Highest possible tap step position, advance from neutral.
The attribute shall be greater than lowStep.

label: gPerSection
comment: Positive sequence shunt (charging) conductance per section.

label: ratedIdc
comment: Rated converter DC current, also called IdN. The attribute shall be a positive value. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow.

label: CogenerationPlant
comment: A thermal generating unit may be a member of a cogeneration plant.

label: y2value
comment: The data value of the second Y-axis variable (if present), depending on the Y-axis units.

label: length
comment: Segment length for calculating line section capabilities.

label: LoadGroup
comment: Group of this ConformLoad.

label: g
comment: Positive sequence shunt conductance.

label: value2Unit
comment: Value2 units of measure.

label: normallyInService
comment: Specifies the availability of the equipment under normal operating conditions. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

label: IntervalSchedule
comment: Regular interval schedule containing this time point.

label: ratedUdc
comment: Rated DC device voltage. The attribute shall be a positive value. It is configuration data used in power flow.

label: x
comment: Positive sequence series reactance (star-model) of the transformer end.

label: ratio
comment:
The voltage at the tap step divided by rated voltage of the transformer end having the tap changer. Hence this is a value close to one.
For example, if the ratio at step 1 is 1.01, and the rated voltage of the transformer end is 110kV, then the voltage obtained by setting the tap changer to step 1 to is 111.1kV.

label: neutralU
comment:
Voltage at which the winding operates at the neutral tap setting. It is the voltage at the terminal of the PowerTransformerEnd associated with the tap changer when all tap changers on the transformer are at their neutralStep position.  Normally neutralU of the tap changer is the same as ratedU of the PowerTransformerEnd, but it can differ in special cases such as when the tapping mechanism is separate from the winding more common on lower voltage transformers.
This attribute is not relevant for PhaseTapChangerAsymmetrical, PhaseTapChangerSymmetrical and PhaseTapChangerLinear.

label: ratedE
comment: Full energy storage capacity of the battery. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: lowVoltageLimit
comment:
The bus bar's low voltage limit.
The limit applies to all equipment and nodes contained in a given VoltageLevel. It is not required that it is exchanged in pair with highVoltageLimit. It is preferable to use operational VoltageLimit, which prevails, if present.

label: regulationCapability
comment: Specifies whether or not the EquivalentInjection has the capability to regulate the local voltage. If true the EquivalentInjection can regulate. If false the EquivalentInjection cannot regulate. ReactiveCapabilityCurve can only be associated with EquivalentInjection  if the flag is true.

label: TapChangerControl
comment: The regulating control scheme in which this tap changer participates.

label: Season
comment: Season for the Schedule.

label: OperationalLimitType
comment: The limit type associated with this limit.

label: x
comment: Positive sequence series reactance of the entire line section.

label: longPF
comment: Generating unit long term economic participation factor.

label: toEndIsoCode
comment:
The ISO code of the region which the "To" side of the Boundary point belongs to or is connected to.
The ISO code is a two-character country code as defined by ISO 3166 (http://www.iso.org/iso/country_codes). The length of the string is 2 characters maximum.

label: ratedUdc
comment: Rated converter DC voltage, also called UdN. The attribute shall be a positive value. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. For instance a bipolar HVDC link with value  200 kV has a 400kV difference between the dc lines.

label: r
comment: Positive sequence series resistance of the entire line section.

label: kind
comment: Types of limits defined in the ENTSO-E Operational Handbook Policy 3.

label: resistiveLoss
comment: It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. Refer to poleLossP. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: minQ
comment: Minimum reactive power limit for the unit.

label: windingConnectionAngle
comment: The phase angle between the in-phase winding and the out-of -phase winding used for creating phase shift. The out-of-phase winding produces what is known as the difference voltage.  Setting this angle to 90 degrees is not the same as a symmetrical transformer. The attribute can only be multiples of 30 degrees.  The allowed range is -150 degrees to 150 degrees excluding 0.

label: fromEndNameTso
comment: Identifies the name of the transmission system operator, distribution system operator or other entity at which the "From" side of the interconnection is connected to. The length of the string is 64 characters maximum.

label: ratedU
comment:
Rated voltage (nameplate data, Ur in IEC 60909-0). It is primarily used for short circuit data exchange according to IEC 60909.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: normalValue
comment: The normal limit on voltage. High or low limit nature of the limit depends upon the properties of the operational limit type. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: RatioTapChangerTable
comment: Table of this point.

label: sequenceNumber
comment: The position of the regular time point in the sequence. Note that time points don't have to be sequential, i.e. time points may be omitted. The actual time for a RegularTimePoint is computed by multiplying the associated regular interval schedule's time step with the regular time point sequence number and adding the associated schedules start time. To specify values for the start time, use sequence number 0.  The sequence number cannot be negative.

label: pVoltageExponent
comment: Exponent of per unit voltage effecting real power.

label: DCConductingEquipment
comment: A DC converter terminal belong to an DC converter.

label: Terminal
comment: The terminal where the operational limit set apply.

label: r
comment: Positive sequence resistance.

label: bch
comment: Positive sequence shunt (charging) susceptance, uniformly distributed, of the entire line section.  This value represents the full charging over the full length of the line.

label: startTime
comment: The time for the first time point.  The value can be a time of day, not a specific date.

label: minQ
comment: Minimum reactive power of the injection.  Used for modelling of infeed for load flow exchange. Not used for short circuit modelling.  If maxQ and minQ are not used ReactiveCapabilityCurve can be used.

label: pConstantCurrent
comment: Portion of active power load modelled as constant current.

label: b
comment: Positive sequence shunt susceptance.

label: ltcFlag
comment: Specifies whether or not a TapChanger has load tap changing capabilities.

label: minQ
comment: Minimum reactive power limit. It is used for modelling of infeed for load flow exchange and not for short circuit modelling.

label: b
comment:
The magnetizing branch susceptance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual susceptance is calculated as follows:
calculated magnetizing susceptance = b(nominal) * (1 + b(from this class)/100).   The b(nominal) is defined as the static magnetizing susceptance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

label: BusNameMarker
comment: The bus name marker used to name the bus (topological node).

label: mode
comment: The regulating control mode presently available.  This specification allows for determining the kind of regulation without need for obtaining the units from a schedule.

label: xMax
comment: The reactance depends on the tap position according to a "u" shaped curve. The maximum reactance (xMax) appears at the low and high tap positions. Depending on the “u” curve the attribute can be either higher or lower than PowerTransformerEnd.x.

label: pConstantPower
comment: Portion of active power load modelled as constant power.

label: minOperatingP
comment: This is the minimum operating active power limit the dispatcher can enter for this unit.

label: DayType
comment: DayType for the Schedule.

label: energyIdentCodeEic
comment: The attribute is used for an exchange of the EIC code (Energy identification Code). The length of the string is 16 characters as defined by the EIC code. For details on EIC scheme please refer to ENTSO-E web site.

label: PccTerminal
comment: Point of common coupling terminal for this converter DC side. It is typically the terminal on the power transformer (or switch) closest to the AC network.

label: ReportingGroup
comment: The reporting group to which this bus name marker belongs.

label: r
comment: Positive sequence series resistance of the reduced branch.

label: resistance
comment: Resistance of the DC device.

label: TransformerEnd
comment: Transformer end to which this phase tap changer belongs.

label: governorSCD
comment: Power Frequency Bias. This is the change in power injection divided by the change in frequency and negated.  A positive value of the power frequency bias provides additional power injection upon a drop in frequency.

label: CombinedCyclePlant
comment: A thermal generating unit may be a member of a combined cycle plant.

label: EnergyArea
comment: The energy area that is forecast from this control area specification.

label: type
comment: Modes that this synchronous machine can operate in.

label: slope
comment:
The characteristics slope of an SVC defines how the reactive power output changes in proportion to the difference between the regulated bus voltage and the voltage setpoint.
The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: r21
comment:
Resistance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1 .Used for steady state power flow. This attribute is optional and represent unbalanced network such as off-nominal phase shifter. If only EquivalentBranch.r is given, then EquivalentBranch.r21 is assumed equal to EquivalentBranch.r.
Usage rule : EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: maxQ
comment: Maximum reactive power limit. This is the maximum (nameplate) limit for the unit.

label: ConnectivityNodeContainer
comment: Container of this connectivity node.

label: normalValue
comment: The normal apparent power limit. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero.

label: inductance
comment: Inductance of the DC line segment. Negligible compared with DCSeriesDevice used for smoothing.

label: r
comment:
The resistance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual reactance is calculated as follows:
calculated resistance = r(nominal) * (1 + r(from this class)/100).   The r(nominal) is defined as the static resistance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

label: maximumSections
comment: The maximum number of sections that may be switched in.

label: SolarPowerPlant
comment: A solar power plant may have solar generating units.

label: ConformLoadGroup
comment: The ConformLoadGroup where the ConformLoadSchedule belongs.

label: capacitiveRating
comment: Capacitive reactance at maximum capacitive reactive power.  Shall always be positive.

label: description
comment: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

label: RatioTapChangerTable
comment: The tap ratio table for this ratio  tap changer.

label: g
comment:
The magnetizing branch conductance deviation as a percentage of nominal value. The actual conductance is calculated as follows:
calculated magnetizing conductance = g(nominal) * (1 + g(from this class)/100).   The g(nominal) is defined as the static magnetizing conductance on the associated power transformer end or ends.  This model assumes the star impedance (pi model) form.

label: Region
comment: The sub-geographical region of the line.

label: minQ
comment: Minimum reactive power limit for the unit. This is the minimum (nameplate) limit for the unit.

label: valveU0
comment: Valve threshold voltage, also called Uvalve. Forward voltage drop when the valve is conducting. Used in loss calculations, i.e. the switchLoss depend on numberOfValves * valveU0.

label: value1
comment: The first value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the derived type of the associated schedule.

label: operationMode
comment: The operating mode of an HVDC bipole (bipolar, monopolar metallic return, etc).

label: GeneratingUnit
comment: The generating unit specified for this control area.  Note that a control area should include a GeneratingUnit only once.

label: Terminal
comment: The terminal associated with this regulating control.  The terminal is associated instead of a node, since the terminal could connect into either a topological node or a connectivity node.  Sometimes it is useful to model regulation at a terminal of a bus bar object.

label: EquipmentContainer
comment: Container of this equipment.

label: xMin
comment: The reactance depends on the tap position according to a "u" shaped curve. The minimum reactance (xMin) appears at the mid tap position.  PowerTransformerEnd.x shall be consistent with PhaseTapChangerLinear.xMin and PhaseTapChangerNonLinear.xMin. In case of inconsistency, PowerTransformerEnd.x shall be used.

label: HydroPowerPlant
comment: The hydro generating unit belongs to a hydro power plant.

label: RegulatingControl
comment: The regulating control scheme in which this equipment participates.

label: GeneratingUnit
comment: A generating unit may have a gross active power to net active power curve, describing the losses and auxiliary power requirements of the unit.

label: phases
comment:
Represents the normal network phasing condition. If the attribute is missing, three phases (ABC) shall be assumed, except for terminals of grounding classes (specializations of EarthFaultCompensator, GroundDisconnector, and Ground) which will be assumed to be N. Therefore, phase code ABCN is explicitly declared when needed, e.g. for star point grounding equipment.
The phase code on terminals connecting same ConnectivityNode or same TopologicalNode as well as for equipment between two terminals shall be consistent.

label: energyConversionCapability
comment: Energy conversion capability for generating.

label: TapChanger
comment: A TapSchedule is associated with a TapChanger.

label: baseS
comment: Base apparent power of the converter pole. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: shortName
comment: The attribute is used for an exchange of a human readable short name with length of the string 12 characters maximum.

label: CAESPlant
comment: A thermal generating unit may be a member of a compressed air energy storage plant.

label: inductance
comment: Inductance to ground.

label: lengthFromTerminal1
comment: The length to the place where the cut is located starting from side one of the cut line segment, i.e. the line segment Terminal with sequenceNumber equal to 1.

label: toEndNameTso
comment: Identifies the name of the transmission system operator, distribution system operator or other entity at which the "To" side of the interconnection is connected to. The length of the string is 64 characters maximum.

label: connectionKind
comment: Kind of connection.

label: x21
comment:
Reactance from terminal sequence 2 to terminal sequence 1. Used for steady state power flow. This attribute is optional and represents an unbalanced network such as off-nominal phase shifter. If only EquivalentBranch.x is given, then EquivalentBranch.x21 is assumed equal to EquivalentBranch.x.
Usage rule: EquivalentBranch is a result of network reduction prior to the data exchange.

label: qfixed
comment: Reactive power of the load that is a fixed quantity and does not vary as load group value varies. Load sign convention is used, i.e. positive sign means flow out from a node.

label: acceptableDuration
comment: The nominal acceptable duration of the limit. Limits are commonly expressed in terms of the time limit for which the limit is normally acceptable. The actual acceptable duration of a specific limit may depend on other local factors such as temperature or wind speed. The attribute has meaning only if the flag isInfiniteDuration is set to false, hence it shall not be exchanged when isInfiniteDuration is set to true.

label: endTime
comment: The time for the last time point.  The value can be a time of day, not a specific date.

label: BaseVoltage
comment: The base voltage used for all equipment within the voltage level.

label: x
comment: Positive sequence series reactance of the reduced branch.

label: ratedGrossMaxP
comment:
The unit's gross rated maximum capacity (book value).
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: Terminal
comment: The Terminal at the equipment where the AuxiliaryEquipment is attached.

label: ratedCurrent
comment:
The maximum continuous current carrying capacity in amps governed by the device material and construction.
The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: r
comment: Resistance to ground.

label: maxP
comment: Maximum active power limit. The value is overwritten by values of VsCapabilityCurve, if present.

label: stepVoltageIncrement
comment:
Tap step increment, in per cent of rated voltage of the power transformer end, per step position.
When the increment is negative, the voltage decreases when the tap step increases.

label: nominalSpeed
comment: Nameplate data.  Depends on the slip and number of pole pairs.

label: aVRDelay
comment: An automatic voltage regulation delay (AVRDelay) which is the time delay from a change in voltage to when the capacitor is allowed to change state. This filters out temporary changes in voltage.

label: xMin
comment: The reactance depend on the tap position according to a "u" shaped curve. The minimum reactance (xMin) appear at the mid tap position.   PowerTransformerEnd.x shall be consistent with PhaseTapChangerLinear.xMin and PhaseTapChangerNonLinear.xMin. In case of inconsistency, PowerTransformerEnd.x shall be used.

label: minUdc
comment: The minimum voltage on the DC side at which the converter should operate. It is converter’s configuration data used in power flow. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: value1Unit
comment: Value1 units of measure.

label: maxOperatingP
comment: This is the maximum operating active power limit the dispatcher can enter for this unit.

label: CapabilityCurve
comment: Capability curve of this converter.

label: ReactiveCapabilityCurve
comment: The reactive capability curve used by this equivalent injection.
